==Demographics==
The [[United States Census Bureau|Census Bureau]] began tracking Fedora as part of a [[Census-designated place|CDP]] which bears its name, in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/cf/1.0/en/place/Fedora%20CDP,%20South%20Dakota/POPULATION/DECENNIAL_CNT|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212083526/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/cf/1.0/en/place/Fedora%20CDP,%20South%20Dakota/POPULATION/DECENNIAL_CNT|url-status=dead|archive-date=12 February 2020|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=29 November 2014|title=American FactFinder}}</ref> The population of the CDP was 26 at the [[2020 United States Census|2020 census]].<ref name=USCensus>{{cite web |title=U.S. Census Bureau: Fedora CDP, South Dakota |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/profile?g=1600000US4621340 |website=www.census.gov |publisher=United States Census Bureau |access-date=16 January 2022 |language=en}}</ref>

